  <h2>Why Remove Special Characters?</h2>
  <p>Special characters (@, #, $, %, &, !, ?) can cause problems in:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Databases</strong> — Certain characters require escaping, causing errors</li>
    <li><strong>File names</strong> — Most operating systems restrict special characters in files</li>
    <li><strong>URLs</strong> — Special characters need percent-encoding</li>
    <li><strong>APIs</strong> — Many APIs reject input with unescaped special characters</li>
    <li><strong>CSV/Excel imports</strong> — Special characters can break data parsing</li>
    <li><strong>Programming</strong> — Code often requires alphanumeric-only variable names</li>
  </ul>

