  <h2>Remove Special Characters for Different Use Cases</h2>

  <h3>Database Import</h3>
  <p>Before importing user-generated data into a database, use our <a href="/tools/remove-special-characters/">special character remover</a> to ensure compatibility. Special characters like single quotes can break SQL queries if not properly escaped.</p>

  <h3>File Naming</h3>
  <p>Operating systems restrict certain characters in file names. Clean your file names with our tool before creating new files. Windows doesn't allow: &lt; &gt; : " / \ | ? * </p>

  <h3>API Data Preparation</h3>
  <p>APIs often reject input with unescaped special characters. Pre-clean your data with our tool to reduce API errors and improve request success rates.</p>

  <h3>CSV Data Cleaning</h3>
  <p>CSVs with uncleaned special characters can misparse during import. Use our <a href="/tools/remove-special-characters/">remover</a> to normalize data before Excel or database import.</p>

